KwaZulu-Natal police have on Monday confirmed that three family members have been shot dead in Folweni. It is alleged that the family members were in their vehicle when they were attacked by unknown suspects who opened fire on Sunday night. “Three died instantly on the scene and three others sustained injuries and were taken to hospital for treatment,” said Police spokesperson Thulani Zwane. This is the third incident where family members are gunned down in the province. Last week, eight family members were gunned down during an attack on their two rondavels in the Embangweni village. While five relatives were shot dead in Nteke area, Mariannhill. -TNA Reporter 